        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 19 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 615 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
McCamey, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
McCamey, Rankin, and Upton County Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
western Texas.</instruction>
